The paper proposes a novel distributed space-time block code (STBC) for mobile TV broadcasting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. The code is designed to improve the performance of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC) categories. The code also shows strong adaptivity to single frequency network broadcasting deployments, which involves system-level optimization (cs.SY).
